        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:46PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of gusty
thunderstorms extending from near Baker to 26 miles south of
Ashland, or extending from near Baker to 37 miles west of Broadus,
moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Baker, Broadus, Ekalaka, Ridgeway, Biddle, Powderville, Boyes,
Hammond, Belle Creek, Olive, Belltower, Medicine Rocks State Park,
Mill Iron, Willard, Sonnette, Webster, Moorhead and Otter.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
